litics, and ethics. This class does not require any background in rhetoric, digital studies, or multimodal composing.", "student_sets": [{"id": 896, "name": "undergraduate"}], "offering_tags": [{"name": "intermittent", "type": "INFO"}], "website": null, "instructors": [], "is_repeatable": false, "is_req_repeatable": false, "repeat_limit_attempts": null, "repeat_limit_credits": null, "catalog_levels": [], "skills": [{"name": "Pedagogy", "slug": "pedagogy", "id": 115}], "attributes": [{"name": "discussion intensive", "id": 2, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "diversity", "id": 3, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "entrepreneurship", "id": 4, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "ethics", "id": 5, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "interdisciplinary", "id": 10, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "communication & presentation", "id": 19, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "collaboration & teamwork", "id": 21, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "intercultural & global lrng", "id": 22, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "equity & inclusion", "id": 23, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "information & data literacy", "id": 20, "type": "attribute"}], "custom_fields": {"goals": "By the end of the course, students will learn to articulate who audiences are, differentiate between users and audiences, analyze their needs using various research methods and technologies, develop interdisciplinary skills to identify and provide for diverse audience needs and expectations.", "key_topics": "user experience, responsible technology design, data analytics", "prerequisite_knowledge": "No prior knowledge necessary", "assessment_structure": "Assignments such as user analysis/experience research, designing chatbots, usability testing reports, and reflective essays.", "relevance": "The course is designed for people interested in understanding of audiences of users and want to design tools and information for diverse population groups in more meaningful ways.", "learning_resources": "Readings, training videos, and in-class w